#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:6
msgid "The Samsung S5P/Exynos4 FIMC driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:8
msgid "Copyright |copy| 2012 - 2013 Samsung Electronics Co., Ltd."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:10
msgid ""
"The FIMC (Fully Interactive Mobile Camera) device available in Samsung SoC "
"Application Processors is an integrated camera host interface, color space "
"converter, image resizer and rotator.  It's also capable of capturing data "
"from LCD controller (FIMD) through the SoC internal writeback data path.  "
"There are multiple FIMC instances in the SoCs (up to 4), having slightly "
"different capabilities, like pixel alignment constraints, rotator "
"availability, LCD writeback support, etc. The driver is located at drivers/"
"media/platform/samsung/exynos4-is directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:20
msgid "Supported SoCs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:22
msgid "S5PC100 (mem-to-mem only), S5PV210, Exynos4210"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:25
msgid "Supported features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:27
msgid "camera parallel interface capture (ITU-R.BT601/565);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:28
msgid "camera serial interface capture (MIPI-CSI2);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:29
msgid ""
"memory-to-memory processing (color space conversion, scaling, mirror and "
"rotation);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:31
msgid ""
"dynamic pipeline re-configuration at runtime (re-attachment of any FIMC "
"instance to any parallel video input or any MIPI-CSI front-end);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:33
msgid "runtime PM and system wide suspend/resume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:36
msgid "Not currently supported"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:38
msgid "LCD writeback input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:39
msgid "per frame clock gating (mem-to-mem)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:42
msgid "User space interfaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:45
msgid "Media device interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:47
msgid ""
"The driver supports Media Controller API as defined at :ref:"
"`media_controller`. The media device driver name is \"Samsung S5P FIMC\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:50
msgid ""
"The purpose of this interface is to allow changing assignment of FIMC "
"instances to the SoC peripheral camera input at runtime and optionally to "
"control internal connections of the MIPI-CSIS device(s) to the FIMC entities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:54
msgid ""
"The media device interface allows to configure the SoC for capturing image "
"data from the sensor through more than one FIMC instance (e.g. for "
"simultaneous viewfinder and still capture setup)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:58
msgid ""
"Reconfiguration is done by enabling/disabling media links created by the "
"driver during initialization. The internal device topology can be easily "
"discovered through media entity and links enumeration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:63
msgid "Memory-to-memory video node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:65
msgid ""
"V4L2 memory-to-memory interface at /dev/video? device node.  This is "
"standalone video device, it has no media pads. However please note the mem-"
"to-mem and capture video node operation on same FIMC instance is not "
"allowed.  The driver detects such cases but the applications should prevent "
"them to avoid an undefined behaviour."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:72
msgid "Capture video node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:74
msgid ""
"The driver supports V4L2 Video Capture Interface as defined at :ref:"
"`devices`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:77
msgid ""
"At the capture and mem-to-mem video nodes only the multi-planar API is "
"supported. For more details see: :ref:`planar-apis`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:81
msgid "Camera capture subdevs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:83
msgid ""
"Each FIMC instance exports a sub-device node (/dev/v4l-subdev?), a sub-"
"device node is also created per each available and enabled at the platform "
"level MIPI-CSI receiver device (currently up to two)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:88
msgid "sysfs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:90
msgid ""
"In order to enable more precise camera pipeline control through the sub-"
"device API the driver creates a sysfs entry associated with \"s5p-fimc-md\" "
"platform device. The entry path is: /sys/platform/devices/s5p-fimc-md/"
"subdev_conf_mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:94
msgid ""
"In typical use case there could be a following capture pipeline "
"configuration: sensor subdev -> mipi-csi subdev -> fimc subdev -> video node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:97
msgid ""
"When we configure these devices through sub-device API at user space, the "
"configuration flow must be from left to right, and the video node is "
"configured as last one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/fimc.rst:101
msgid ""
"When we don't use sub-device user space API the whole configuration of all "
"devices belonging to the pipeline is done at the video node driver. The "
"sysfs entry allows to instruct the capture node driver not to configure the "
"sub-devices (format, crop), to avoid resetting the subdevs' configuration "
"when the last configuration steps at the video node is performed."
msgstr ""

